Title: THE WAR IN ARKANSAS.
Abstract: Advices from Camden, Arkansas, say that Gen. STEELE'S army is there. Gen. THAYER joined Gen. STEELE at Elkin's Ferry, on the Little Missouri River, where the rebels were driven from a line of breastworks commanding the river bottom.
